    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-11-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-11-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="410" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d410">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Bigelow</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 309.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-11-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 14, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have received your despatch of the 18th
                            of October, No. 186, in which you give me the substance of a
                            conversation held between yourself and <pb facs="0505" n="423" xml:id="pg_423"/> Mr. Drouyn de Lhuys on the 17th ultimo, upon the
                            subject of the re-enforcement of the French army in Mexico by recruiting
                            troops in Egypt.</p>
                <p>You are instructed to say to Mr. Drouyn de Lhuys that the disposition of
                            this matter by the Emperor’s government is received with sincere
                            satisfaction by the government of the United States.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Bigelow,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
